Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe state on Wednesday approved the appointment of Dr. Mohammed Goje as the Executive Secretary, Yobe State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA). In a statement by the Information Officer of Yobe state Head of Service, Hussaini Mai Suleh, he said the appointment takes immediate effect. “Until his appointment, Dr. Mohammed Goje was the state Humanitarian/Vaccine Analyst with Clinton Health Access Initiative (CHAI), supporting Bill and Melinda Gates (BMGF) tripartite grant in Yobe state”, the statement read. Yobe governor appoints chief of staff Yobe: Buni retains Gaidam’s SSG Gov. Mai Mala retains Gaidam's SSG Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin